    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-07-18T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-07-18T14:00:00-05:00" n="184"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d184">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/5896</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-07-18T20:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 18, 1917, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received July 18, 5.43 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6767. The Allied War Conference will meet in Paris July 25. British delegates
                    leave London Monday morning. Since the President does not wish to appoint
                    delegates I venture the suggestion that <persName corresp="#p_SAWS1">Admiral
                        Sims</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_PGJJ1">General Pershing</persName>
                    be permitted to attend the conference as visitors. I am privately informed that
                    this would please the British Government. Discussions of military subjects are
                    likely to occur that it would be advantageous and perhaps necessary for our
                    officers to hear. An invitation will be given to them to sit with the conference
                    if this suggestion commends itself to the President, and be quickly
                    received.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
